trend_summary: Built-up area steadily radiates from the central corridor, replacing farmland with curvilinear housing tracts and roadside commerce. Impervious cover rises yet green buffers and water bodies remain. Highway upgrades spur ribbon development, but no high-rise core forms; growth pattern reflects continuing low-rise suburban expansion.
notable_changes: Progressive infill of north-eastern and southern farmland by new residential subdivisions.
East-west arterial widened and new interchanges added, encouraging adjacent commercial strips.
Expansion of light-industrial/commercial roofs around the central junction.
Forest patches in the south-west partially re-established as some fields are abandoned.
Clearing and landscaping along the reservoir shoreline for recreational use.
